The paper deals with algorithms for solving parity games, which are a well-studied class of games in computer science. The focus of the paper is on graphs with bounded treewidth and DAG width, which are important graph parameters in algorithm design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and its parallelizability, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper uses techniques from logic and graph theory, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
